 Unauthorized access must be prevented.

 Reliability

 The system should operate without data loss.
 User data should be stored securely.

Availability

 The application should be available 24×7.
 System uptime should be maintained at 99.9%.

 Scalability

 The system should support increasing numbers of users and posts.

 Usability

 The interface should be user-friendly and easy to navigate.

 Compatibility

The application should support Android, iOS, and Web platforms.


3.6 Inverse Requirements

 The system shall not allow users to access another user's private information without authorization.
 The system shall not allow login with invalid credentials.
 The system shall not allow duplicate usernames or email addresses during registration.
 The system shall not allow users to modify or delete content belonging to other users.
 The system shall not display private account content to unauthorized users.
 The system shall not store user passwords in plain text format.
 The system shall not permit unauthorized access to the database.

 3.7 Design Constraints

 The application shall require an active internet connection for most features.
 The system shall comply with data privacy and security regulations.
 The application shall support Android, iOS, and Web platforms.
 Media uploads shall be restricted to supported file formats only.
 The system shall enforce password and authentication policies.
 Storage and server resources shall be limited based on system capacity.
 Users shall be required to follow community guidelines and content policies.


